<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>A father has faced court accused of sexually assaulting his own nine-year-old daughter more than two years ago.</p>

<p>The father, whose identity cannot be revealed, is accused of inappropriately touching the girl on September 20, 2018.</p>

<p>He pleaded not guilty on Tuesday to one count of indecent dealing with a child under 10 years in the Supreme Court of the Northern Territory. </p>

<p>A man has faced court after he allegedly sexually assaulted his own nine-year-old daughter (stock image)</p>

<p>The court heard the accused man was laying on a mattress with his wife and daughter in a remote community about 200km from Alice Springs, when the alleged incident occurred. </p>

<p>Two other people were also said to be in the same room at the time of the assault. </p>

<p>The young victim was said to be fully clothed when her father allegedly reached over past his sleeping wife to where their daughter lay.</p>

<p>He is then alleged to have inappropriately touched her.</p>

<p>The court heard DNA examinations of the girl and her clothing, which were conducted soon after the alleged incident, did not find sufficient evidence of other DNA components. </p>

<p>The trial continues over the next few days.</p>

<p>The trial for the man is being staged at the Supreme Court of the Northern Territory (stock image)</p>
